%[text] # Programmatic Simulation
%[text] ## Set up the simulation
%[text] To set up the simulation we need to define a Simulation Input Object. In there we need to define the parameters we want to test. The Property Inspector helps us find the names of the blocks and parameters which we need to alter programmatically. See [https://www.mathworks.com/help/simulink/slref/block-parameters-and-properties.html](https://www.mathworks.com/help/simulink/slref/block-parameters-and-properties.html)
%[text] ![](text:image:5ba9)
%[text] In addition to defining block parameters we also give a handle to a PostSim function. This function makes sure that the data produced by the simulation is properly post-processed after the simulation has finished.
simInput = Simulink.SimulationInput("MidSideProcessor_ProgSim_Solution");
simInput = setBlockParameter(simInput, "MidSideProcessor_ProgSim_Solution/Width", "Value", num2str(0.4));
simInput = setPostSimFcn(simInput, @myPostSim);

%%
%[text] ## Start the simulation
simOutput = sim(simInput);
%%
%[text] ## Helper functions
%[text] The `myPostSim` function is provided for you below.
function modOutput = myPostSim(simOutput) 
    modOutput = simOutput;
    fs = simOutput.fs(1);
    modOutput.fs = fs;

    [fpath, ~, ~] = fileparts(simOutput.SimulationMetadata.ModelInfo.ModelFilePath);
    fname = strrep(sprintf("renderedAudio_%1.2f", simOutput.width),".","pt");
    fname = fullfile(fpath, "data", fname + ".wav");
    modOutput.fname = fname;
    
    audiowrite(fname, simOutput.audio, fs)
    
    
end


